    <item>
      <title>Phase 1 : Core networking concepts</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/networking/phase1-core-ntw-concepts/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 19 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/networking/phase1-core-ntw-concepts/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-what-is-a-network&#34;&gt;&lt;font color=&#34;BlueViolet&#34;&gt;1️⃣ What Is a Network?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;simple-definition&#34;&gt;Simple definition:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A network is a group of devices that can communicate with each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;examples-of-devices&#34;&gt;Examples of devices:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Laptop&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Phone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Server&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Printer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Router&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;If devices can send and receive data, they are on a network.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;real-life-analogy&#34;&gt;Real-life analogy&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Think of a network like a postal system:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Houses = devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Addresses = IP addresses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Letters = data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post office = router&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;2-what-is-a-host&#34;&gt;&lt;font color=&#34;BlueViolet&#34;&gt; 2️⃣ What Is a Host?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;definition&#34;&gt;Definition:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A host is any device that can send or receive data on a network.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
